# SECTION: Budgeting and Expense Management

## Summary
A budget helps allocate income across needs, wants, and savings. Effective budgeting ensures financial goals are met without overspending.

## Budgeting Rule (50-30-20)
- 50% → Needs (rent, food, utilities)
- 30% → Wants (entertainment, lifestyle)
- 20% → Savings

## Expense Categories
- Fixed: rent, school fees
- Variable: groceries, transport
- Discretionary: entertainment

## Budgeting Process
1. List income sources
2. Track expenses
3. Categorize spending
4. Adjust spending to fit goals

## Tools
- Mobile apps
- Spreadsheets
- Manual tracking

## Risks
- Underestimating expenses
- Lifestyle inflation
- Poor tracking habits

## Optimization Tips
- Reduce discretionary spending
- Negotiate fixed costs
- Track daily expenses